article.headline: E. Illinois 83, Murray St. 80
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Freshman Tyler Laser had a career-high 27 points to lead Eastern Illinois to an 83-80 overtime win over Murray State on Thursday night. Laser scored six points in overtime, including two free-throws with four seconds left that iced the game for Eastern Illinois (2-11). Julio Anthony added 15 points and Bobby Catchings and Romain Martin each added 10 points for the Panthers, who snapped an eleven-game losing streak. Laser hit two free-throws to give Eastern Illinois a 71-68 lead with five seconds left in regulation. But Murray State's Tyler Holloway sank a 3-pointer as time expired to send the game into overtime. Danero Thomas led Murray State (5-7) with 18 points and Holloway and Tony Easley added 15 points apiece. Eastern Illinois led 31-25 at the half and never trailed in a game that had just two ties.
